{
  "texts": [
    "However, UDG preferentially cleaves a glycosidic bond in deoxyuridine in NdU[G/C] contexts compared with [A/T] dU[A/T] contexts (N represents any base nucleotide) 9.",
    "FFPE-induced mutational signature is similar to SBS1 and SBS30, in which NC>TG and NC>TA contexts are predominant 4.",
    "Thus, UDG treatment could ineffectively remove uracil in certain contexts.",
    "High-fidelity polymerase Pfu could be used to mitigate the risk of incorporating adenine base opposite to uracil 10.",
    "A bioinformatic approach can be applied for accurate variant calling."
  ]
}